  "text": "(D) CD4 À CD8 À CD25 À CD44 À DN4 cells were purified from day 17 fetal thymocytes by depleting the cells expressing CD4, CD8, CD25, or CD44, infected with indicated retroviruses, and reconstituted in FTOC for 2 d; n ¼ 4. Bar graphs show means 6 standard errors. NS, not significant (p ! 0.05); * p , 0.05; ** p , 0.01. DOI: 10.1371/journal.pbio.0040103.g005 The reduced survival of the IL-2-withdrawn 23-1-8 T cells by IAN5 shRNA was markedly restored by the additional expression of Bcl-xL ( Figure 7D ). The overexpression of Bcl-xL failed to inhibit the apoptosis of 23-1-8 T cells induced by helenalin ( Figure 7D) , an inducer of caspase-dependent apoptosis that occurs independent of Bcl-2-family-mediated mitochondrial signals [CITATION_1] , indicating that the Bcl-xL-mediated restoration of cell survival is specific for mitochondrial apoptosis [CITATION_2] . These results indicate that the Bcl-xL overexpression specifically interferes with the enhanced apoptosis by IAN5 knockdown, suggesting the role of Bcl-2 family proteins in the IAN5-mediated regulation of T cell survival.",
